.TH "alloc_io_space" 9 "alloc_io_space" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
alloc_io_space \- allocate IO ports for use by a PCMCIA device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" alloc_io_space
.BI "(struct pcmcia_socket *s "  ","
.BI "struct resource *res "  ","
.BI "unsigned int lines "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "s" 12
pcmcia socket
.IP "res" 12
resource to allocate (begin: begin, end: size)
.IP "lines" 12
number of IO lines decoded by the PCMCIA card
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Special stuff for managing IO windows, because they are scarce
